cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a new approach to train deep neural networks using dictionary learning as the basic building block. This involves using features from shallower layers as inputs for training the next deeper layer. The paper also compares the proposed framework with existing state-of-the-art deep learning techniques on benchmark problems related to computer vision and natural language processing, which suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
